description.narrative: 2019 was marked by education policy advancement for most vulnerable children and improved school practices in drop-out prevention and inclusive education. During 2019 UNICEF has advanced the reforms in quality preschool education with assessment framework and curricula program for 5-6 years old approved. UNICEF has continued to play a leadership role in education sector, leading the education sector donor group, process of sector strategy review, and emergency coordination. UNICEF has responded timely to emergency needs of children by ensuring the continuation of education provision for the affected children through setting up temporary learning spaces. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/01/2020
